{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/notes/neumorphism/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Chandler Moisen","author":"Chandler Moisen"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7c352041-ce41-5ee6-8cfa-23c6dc613217","excerpt":"Today I learned what neumorphism is.Well, rather, I finally learned what this design trend I have been seeing for months on my Muzli feed is called.The term is…","html":"<p>Today I learned what neumorphism is.</p>\n<p>Well, rather, I finally learned what this design trend I have been seeing for months on my <a href=\"https://muz.li/\">Muzli</a> feed is called.</p>\n<p>The term is a weak portmanteau of “new” and “skeuomorphism” - a design pattern where elements of a graphical user interface imitate their RL equivalent in either appearance or interaction.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/24c6db1b6758aab76f2ba0cb70060a79/9fa68/skeuomorphism.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 56.21212121212121%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"examples of skeuomorphism\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/24c6db1b6758aab76f2ba0cb70060a79/c739e/skeuomorphism.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/24c6db1b6758aab76f2ba0cb70060a79/8ee9c/skeuomorphism.jpg 148w,\n/static/24c6db1b6758aab76f2ba0cb70060a79/ebbe7/skeuomorphism.jpg 295w,\n/static/24c6db1b6758aab76f2ba0cb70060a79/c739e/skeuomorphism.jpg 590w,\n/static/24c6db1b6758aab76f2ba0cb70060a79/9fa68/skeuomorphism.jpg 660w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>Neumorphism is a visual design pattern where shadows are used to create the illusion of extruding shapes. These extrusions share the same coloring as their parent element.</p>\n<p>You can see an example of this technique using this <a href=\"https://neumorphism.io/#950451\">generator</a>.</p>\n<p>As I am but a fledging designer, I lack the vocabulary to accurately critique this pattern, but it reminds me of pressing a shape through one of those elastic exercise bands. While certainly eye-catching, I am not sure of its applications in UI design as it makes all elements resemble button and would likely confuse users on what exactly they are supposed to interact with.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Neumorphism","date":"May 21, 2020","isTIL":true}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/neumorphism/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/mock-low-assert-high/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Mock Low, Assert High"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-give-box-shadow-border-radius/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to Give Box Shadow a Border Radius"}}}}}